 Port Elizabeth - Four male suspects, aged between 23 and 30, were arrested in Motherwell, Port Elizabeth, after being found in possession of an unlicensed firearm and ammunition in their vehicle. "This followed after alert SAPS Flying Squad members noticed a suspicious charcoal Datsun Go driving without number plates in Nzunga Street, NU5, Motherwell at about 12:00 on Moonday," described police spokesperson, Captain Andre Beetge.."On searching the vehicle, an unlicenced 9mm pistol (with its serial number removed) and two rounds of ammunition was found on the passenger side floor." He said that all four male occupants were arrested, but three were later released. "The remaining 25-year-old suspect was charged for possession of an unlicensed firearm and ammunition and will be appearing before the Motherwell Magistrates Court on Wednesday." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 